While [[Pontis]] felt vibrant and alive with the constant movement of trade ships, colorful markets, and the hum of different cultures intermingling, Passerelle feels like a city caught between the past and the present, its architectural wonders indifferent to their new rulers.

Approach

The city straddles the mighty Greenwater River. There are two roads that join before leading to the southern gate, the one leading to [[Greenwater Village]], and another that leads to the [[Ruined Bridge of Sorrows]]. The air is thick with mist that drifts in from the swamps to the south, clinging to the stone walls and spires.

As you near the city gates, the old Empires architecture dominates the skylineimposing structures of stone and iron. Passerelles towers and walls are masterpieces of an earlier time, marked with intricate carvings and now adorned with the banners of their orcish conquerors.

Riverside

Unlike the lively docks of [[Pontis]], filled with ships from every corner of the realm, Passerelles riverside is quieter, with fewer boats and more watchful eyes. The docks are utilitarian and worn, used more for military logistics than trade. The river flows dark and steady, a lifeline that has seen the city through countless sieges.

[[The Gutters End tavern]] can be found here. 

Backstreets

The buildings of Passerelle are tall and closely packed, with narrow alleyways that twist unpredictably between them. Many structures bear the scars of past battlescrumbling facades, scorch marks, and hastily patched walls. Here and there, signs of rebellion and defiance still linger: faded symbols of the [[The Holy Shard Empire | Empire]], and graffiti protesting the [[Urokgard]] rule.
